title: Spain: Two million Catalans demand independence on Barcelona streets
description:
Video ID: 20140911-044

W/S Crowd gathering on Gran Via street 
M/S Pro-independence people marching 
M/S People waving Pro-independence flag (Estelada)
M/S People marching 
M/S Choir singing
W/S Choir singing
M/S Girl holding independence flag 
SOT, Julia Dalma, demonstrator (in English): "Yeah, we are different from Spain and it is like we are free. They want to stay but we don't want to stay with them ."
W/S Crowd gathering on Gran Via street 
SOT Female demonstrator (in English): "We don't feel like we are Spanish, we are Catalan only, not Spanish. We are neighbours, only neighbours, but we don't feel like we are Spanish people. 
Male demonstrator (in English) "Catalonia is the new state of Europe." 
M/S Girl placing vote in ballot box at head of V 
W/S Crowd doing Mexican wave 
W/S People doing human pyramid 
M/S People doing human pyramid 
W/S People doing human pyramid 
W/S Independence flags of Catalonia 

SCRIPT

Almost two million people according to local police gathered in Barcelona on Thursday to celebrate the Catalonian national day and to demand a referendum for the independence of Catalonia. 

Demonstrators marched through Diagonal Street and Gran Via, converging to form the letter "V" for "vote" and "victory". Protesters also waved pro-independence flags and shouted "we want to vote" and "independence". 

Many personalities addressed the crowds from three different stages along the march. Demonstrators explained that they did not feel Spanish and merely viewed Spain as a neighbour but not as part of their national and cultural identity.
